uestions.</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"row\">\n            <div class=\"col-xs-12 text-center\">\n                <ul class=\"faq-list role-element leadstyle-text\"><li><strong><span style=\"color:#46bec2\">Do I need to know how to code?</span></strong><br>Absolutely not! If you&#8217;re a woman who loves nerdy things, design, tech, creativity, or if you just have an awesome idea, please attend this event. Teams need people with all kinds of gifts and abilities, and anyone is welcome.</li><li><strong><span style=\"color:#46bec2\">What should I bring?</span></strong><br>Definitely bring any equipment or tools you plan on using (computers, devices, etc.), but also think about anything to keep you comfy and focused while you&#8217;re awake for 24 hours (comfy clothes, a blanket, headphones).</li><li><strong><span style=\"color:#46bec2\">How do I sign up for this event?</span></strong><br>Just simply click one of the Register buttons above. You&#8217;ll be prompted to select the city you&#8217;d like to attend in, and then you&#8217;ll be taken to a ticket purchasing screen where you can book your spot.</li><li><strong><span style=\"color:#46bec2\">Do I need to sign up with a team?</span></strong><br>No way! We want you to meet new people. After registration, we&#8217;ll do a fun icebreaker and idea generation session. From there, we&#8217;ll divide into teams based on different interest levels and skillsets. We want you to branch out and make new connections.</li><li><strong><span style=\"color:#46bec2\">What do I win?</span></strong><br>We have an awesome awards ceremony with awards that are far from the norm (Most Deserving of a Beer, Nerdiest Project, etc.), but you&#8217;ll also win an excellent portfolio piece and amazing connections within the female tech community.</li><li><strong><span style=\"color:#46bec2\">Is there an age limit?</span></strong><br>This event is open to women ages 21 and above due to the potential consumption 